6848e`) - status: running ✅\n3. `cron:6f3323ef` (key: `agent:master-orchestrator:cron:6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31`) - status: running ✅\n4. `main` (key: `agent:master-orchestrator:main`) - status: done ✅\n\nI also see a planner subagent session that's still running. Now comparing the baseline from 21:37 UTC against the current 22:43 UTC state, most of the cron jobs are still running as expected, though `cron:6f3323ef` has shifted from done back to running. The main session remains done, and the Telegram group session has transitioned from running to done. The cron job cycling between done and running is normal behavior, and the Telegram group session ending is expected. Looking at the remaining sessions, the main session is done, and there are a few zombie sessions from older cron jobs and subagents that didn't clean up properly. None of these represent actual state changes, so the system is stable.\n\nChecking the subagents that have been running within cron:ed2d0b5d, most of them are actually completed or failed rather than still active. The only one still running is cron:e7885813 with its own subagent.\n\nLooking at the overall picture, the baseline sessions from 21:37 UTC are all still present with their expected statuses—cron:ed2d0b5d is running, cron:e7885813 is running, cron:6f3323ef has cycled back to running, and the main session is done. Since everything checks out as normal, there's nothing to report."},{"type":"text","text":"\nSilent — no state changes.\n\n**Baseline (21:37 UTC) vs current (22:43 UTC):**\n\n| Session | Baseline | Current | Δ |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `cron:ed2d0b5d` (QLHV 5p) | running ✅ | running ✅ | — |\n| `cron:e7885813` (Agent Status) | running ✅ | running ✅ | — |\n| `cron:6f3323ef` (DTLX 5p) | **done** | running (new cycle) | Normal cron restart |\n| `main` | done | done | — |\n| `telegram:group:-5163901258` | running (stale) | done (~21:49 UTC) | Already reported |\n\n`cron:6f3323ef` cycling back to \"running\" is normal 5-m